OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F163A1771945433
OL,1,Wj5hw1~{4k7juhw1{$             G2/2
OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Wed 11 Mar to Wed 25 Mar
OL,6,FChangeable conditions will probably
OL,7,Fcontinue to dominate during this
OL,8,Fperiod, with Atlantic frontal systems
OL,9,Fspreading across the UK. These will
OL,10,Fbring spells of rain and perhaps
OL,11,Fstrong winds, with the wettest
OL,12,Fconditions in the northwest, whilst
OL,13,Fthe southeast will likely be driest.
OL,14,FTemperatures are likely to be near to
OL,15,For slightly above normal overall. It
OL,16,Fis possible that longer spells of dry
OL,17,Fweather occur later in the month as
OL,18,Fmore blocked pattern could develop,
OL,19,Fwhich could lead to some colder
OL,20,Fconditions too.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
